  <bioghist id="aspace_d30b2e1ad64886e2f4f2fcec75013193">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Jacob Gould Schurman professor of animal science, Cornell University.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_581a44a731c85e557784d0d41fea293d">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Includes publications, reports, subject files, course material, and proceedings of the Cornell Symposium on Theriogenology honoring Foote, 1992; "Artificial Insemination to Cloning: Tracing 50 Years of Research," 1998; reprint of "Development of Reproductive Biotechnologies in Domestic Animals from Artificial Insemination to Cloning: A Perspective," in Cloning, Vol. 1, Number 3, 1999; Proceedings of the International Symposium: "From the first artificial insemination to the modern reproduction biotechnologies: traditional ways and new frontiers of animal production, Regio Emilia (Italy) October 8-9,1999;" "Highlights in Dairy Cattle Reproduction in the Last 100 Years," 2005. Also articles, video tape, audio tapes, and photograph.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <relatedmaterial id="aspace_bf9fce04d6064bdf4e156a0f63c0a35a">
    <head>RELATED MATERIALS</head>
<p>See also: <extref href="http://ecommons.library.cornell.edu/handle/1813/3759" show="new">Internet First University Press: Animal Reproduction: Reflections by Robert H. Foote, 2006</extref></p>  </relatedmaterial>
